<article id="node-17212">
<h1 >3.15.4.10 Qualification for EMEP</h1>
<h2>Qualification (<a href="../guide-social-security-law/1/1/q/10">1.1.Q.10</a>) criteria</h2>
<p>To qualify for <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#emep" title="Essential medical equipment payment">EMEP</a>, a person must meet the criteria listed in the following table. Where more detail about a criterion is required, the second column indicates where you will find this.</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Criterion</th>
<th scope="col">More Detail</th>
</tr><tr><th colspan="2" scope="col">ALL of the following</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>
<p>The payment is available to people with medical needs, or their carers, who:</p>
<ul><li>use certain essential medical equipment, or have certain medical conditions that require the use of additional heating and/or cooling, in their home, AND</li>
<li>are covered by a Commonwealth Government concession card or a <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#dva" title="Department of Veterans' Affairs">DVA</a> gold or white card, AND</li>
<li>are responsible, either wholly or partly, for meeting the energy costs associated with running the equipment.</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>SS Guide <a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/30">3.15.4.30</a> Types of Claimants - People with Medical Needs &amp; Carers (EMEP)</p>
<p><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/40">3.15.4.40</a> Essential Medical Equipment (EMEP)</p>
<p><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/50">3.15.4.50</a> Qualification for Medically Required Heating or Cooling (EMEP)</p>
<p><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/60">3.15.4.60</a> Concession Card Requirement (EMEP)</p>
<p><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/70">3.15.4.70</a> Energy Account Requirement (EMEP)</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>The residence/s for which EMEP is being claimed is a valid residence for the purposes of EMEP, AND</td>
<td><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/80">3.15.4.80</a> Residences (EMEP)</td>
</tr><tr><td>The medical equipment or medically required heating and/or cooling uses an approved form of energy for EMEP, AND</td>
<td><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/100">3.15.4.100</a> Approved Forms of Energy (EMEP)</td>
</tr><tr><td>The claimant is not a dependent child, AND</td>
<td><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/15/4/30">3.15.4.30</a> Types of Claimants - People with Medical Needs &amp; Carers (EMEP)</td>
</tr><tr><td>The claimant is in Australia.</td>
<td>Â </td>
</tr></tbody></table><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 917B Qualification for essential medical equipment payment, section 917C The medical needs requirement, section 917D The concession card requirement, section 917E(2) The energy account requirement</p>
<p><a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/F2012L00696">Social Security (Essential Medical Equipment Payment - Essential Medical Equipment) Specification 2012</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/F2012L00697">Social Security (Essential Medical Equipment Payment - Medical Conditions) Specification 2012</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/F2012L00695">Social Security (Essential Medical Equipment Payment - Residences) Specification 2012</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/F2012L00694">Social Security (Essential Medical Equipment Payment - Energy) Specification 2012</a></p>
</div>
